There is an easier way to pack your kite.

Deflate your kite, fold it in the middle so the tips are touching and move your way towards them. Now you can easily start rolling from the tips to the middle.

Only one side of the kite touches the sand and when you want to kite the next time it's super easy to unroll.

POV: You're riding two kites 🧐

After an unfortunate accident during a trip with the @thewindseekersrs a friend of mine injured her knee, we had to bring her and the equipment safely back to the the boat. 

We pulled her safety and the kite flipped leading edge down on the water so it stopped pulling her. As the water was shallow I could stand next to her and take both kites (one still on safety line) to make sure she was as comfortable as possible. 

The boat quickly noticed something was wrong and send a zodiac to pick her up. As she was in a lot of pain we decided to prioritize her travel and I would wait for the second zodiac to pick up her kite that I was holding. 

While waiting I had the 💡 idea to ride both kites back 😅 starting was the hardest but I managed to get going both sides and ride the 1,5km back to the main boat.

*** I DO NOT RECOMMEND DOING THIS! ***

Even though everything went well, it isn't exactly easy and can go wrong in many ways. Generally it's best to keep a safe distance from other kites and lines to make sure you dont get tangled and escalate the situation.

I made sure there were no obstacles I could hit, and we had a second safety boat on standby in case I crashed or had to release.

Please act within you abilities and be safe out there 🤙

Turn around in style 🤩

The jump transition is a great way to practice your jumping technique without flying all the way downwind. If you’re able to convert all your speed towards the wind you’ll find that you go straight up and down for an easy transition. 
Applying this technique to your big air riding you’ll find that you go a lot higher and have softer landings. 

Full video can be found through my BIO 🔗
